This paper discusses the publication of open citation data using Semantic Web technologies, which is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. cs.DL (Digital Libraries) is the most likely category as it directly relates to the infrastructure and tools for open scholarship. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) are also likely categories as they deal with data analysis and processing, which are important for bibliometric analysis. cs.DB (Databases) is another relevant category as it discusses the OpenCitations Corpus, which is a database of bibliographic and citation data. Finally, cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is a possible category as it deals with the use of network analysis in bibliometrics.
